cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.MM, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on modeling human language and understanding the nonverbal contexts in which words appear.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the paper analyzes fine-grained visual patterns that occur during word segments.
- cs.SD (Sound) is another possible category as the paper also analyzes acoustic patterns that occur during word segments.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper deals with multimodal sentiment analysis and emotion recognition.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also relevant as the proposed model, RAVEN, is a deep learning model that uses recurrent neural networks and attention mechanisms.
